There are a total of $\binom{9}{2} = 36$ handshakes.  If we draw a graph with each person as a vertex and each handshake as an edge, then we see that every vertex has degree $2,$ and the graph is a collection of disjoint cycles.  (Note that there can be no cycles of length 1, since each person shakes hands with exactly two other people.)

