\begin{align*}
P_n &= \frac13 \cdot P_{n-1} + \frac13 \cdot P_{n-2} + \frac13 \cdot P_{n-2} \\
&= \frac13 \cdot P_{n-1} + \frac23 \cdot P_{n-2}.
\end{align*}
We can easily compute $P_2 = \frac13$ and $P_3 = \frac29$. Continuing, we find that $P_7 = \frac{19}{243}$, so $n = \boxed{019}$.

